## FILE 1: inspo-categories.json ENTRY

Add a new key inside the `"designs": {}` object. The key must match the slug exactly.

### Complete schema with all required fields:

```json
"[slug]": {
  "slug": "[slug]",
  "name": "[Full Display Name]",
  "displayName": "[Full Display Name]",
  "category": "[Category]",
  "year": 2026,
  "active": true,
  "trending": true,
  "clicks": 0,
  "addedAt": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "description": "[One sentence describing the category for the page]",
  "heroImage": "/inspo/[slug].webp",
  "gradientFrom": "[tailwind-color]",
  "gradientVia": "[tailwind-color]",
  "gradientTo": "[tailwind-color]",
  "emojis": ["emoji1", "emoji2", "emoji3", "emoji4"],
  "ctas": ["Label1", "Label2", "Label3", "Label4"],
  "tldr": {
    "summary": [
      "sentence 1 about the category designs",
      "sentence 2 about trending styles",
      "sentence 3 about application/techniques",
      "sentence 4 about occasions/use cases"
    ],
    "keyTakeaways": ["Takeaway 1", "Takeaway 2", "Takeaway 3", "Takeaway 4"]
  },
  "seo": {
    "title": "[Keyword Rich Title] | Mirellé",
    "description": "[150 char SEO meta description with main keywords]",
    "keywords": "keyword1, keyword2, keyword3, keyword4, keyword5, keyword6, keyword7, keyword8, keyword9"
  },
  "relatedDesigns": ["slug-1", "slug-2", "slug-3"],
  "perfectFor": ["Occasion 1", "Occasion 2", "Occasion 3", "Occasion 4"],
  "styleGuide": ["Tip 1", "Tip 2", "Tip 3"]
}
```

### Field rules — read carefully:

| Field | Rule |
|---|---|
| `slug` | lowercase, hyphens only, match exactly with JSON key and image folder name |
| `name` + `displayName` | must be identical |
| `category` | must be one of: `Shape`, `Seasonal`, `Occasion`, `Classic`, `Technique` — OR a new string to create a new section |
| `active` | always `true` for new categories |
| `trending` | `true` for new categories so they appear in carousel |
| `clicks` | always `0` for new categories |
| `addedAt` | today's date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format — controls carousel order, newest shows first |
| `heroImage` | `/inspo/[slug].webp` — must match actual image file in `/public/inspo/` |
| `relatedDesigns` | must be valid slugs that exist in the JSON — never reference a non-existent slug |
| `seo.keywords` | comma-separated string, NOT an array |

